headline: Packaging Corporation of America’s (NYSE:PKG) Q3 Earnings Results: Revenue In Line With Expectations But Stock Drops
summary: Packaging Corporation of America (NYSE:PKG) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 6% year on year to $2.31 billion. Its GAAP profit of $2.51 per share was 11.5% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Packaging Corporation of America Reports Third Quarter 2025 Results
summary: LAKE FOREST, Ill., October 22, 2025--Packaging Corporation of America (NYSE: PKG) today reported third quarter 2025 net income of $226.9 million, or $2.51 per share, and net income of $246.7 million, or $2.73 per share, excluding special items. Third quarter net sales were $2.3 billion in 2025 and $2.2 billion in 2024.

Third quarter net sales were $2.3 billion in 2025 and $2.2 billion in 2024.

headline: Smurfit Westrock removed from price-fixing case, others file for dismissal
summary: Although Smurfit Westrock was dismissed, it’s not entirely out of the woods regarding the containerboard price collusion lawsuit. Separately, other defendants filed individual and collective motions to dismiss.
